According to the plan presented yesterday, the main problem in terms of 1.8 billion tonnes (Gt) of the CFCs emitted to the earth due to lighting would be avoided if the white-hot pears, which so far still represent a monopoly of 50 to 70% on the market, were replaced by fluorescent or better, by light-emitting diodes (LEDs).
